When Augustus was in Spain B.0. 27-25 he received a deputation from the Scythians (cf. Gelonos line 23) offer-ing submission, and in 23 he received similar deputations from the Parthians at Rome. Hence most fix the date of this Ode between 27 and 23 B.c. The definite language, however, of 18 seq. about the ⁴ recent trophies ’ secured from the conquest of Armenia and Parthia points to a later date, for Augustus went to the East B.o. 21, and in B.0. 20 sent an expedition into Armenia under Tiberius and recovered from the Parthians the standards lost by Crassus at Carrhae, receiving the personal submission of Prahates (cf. Ep. 1. 12. 26).
